# Illustration Integration Guidelines

## File Organization
- Store pencil drawings in the [assets/](mdc:assets/) directory
- Use descriptive filenames: `birth-illustration.png`, `college-sketch.jpg`, etc.
- Support common formats: PNG, JPG, SVG
- Optimize images for web (compress without losing quality)

## Replacing Placeholders
To replace illustration placeholders in [index.html](mdc:index.html):

1. **Replace the illustration-placeholder div**:
```html
<div class="card-image">
    <img src="assets/birth-illustration.png" 
         alt="Pencil drawing representing birth chapter" 
         class="timeline-illustration">
</div>
```

2. **Add CSS for illustrations** in [styles.css](mdc:styles.css):
```css
.timeline-illustration {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    transition: var(--transition);
}

.timeline-illustration:hover {
    transform: scale(1.02);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
}
```

## Design Considerations
- **Style**: Pencil-drawing aesthetic should be consistent across all illustrations
- **Size**: Images should be responsive and fit well within card layouts
- **Color**: Consider how illustrations work with the dark blue background
- **Consistency**: Maintain similar artistic style and composition across chapters

## Responsive Behavior
- Images should scale appropriately on mobile devices
- Maintain aspect ratios to prevent distortion
- Consider different image sizes for different screen resolutions